=== 3. REPLACE checkSystemHealth FUNCTION BODY ===

Replace the existing `checkSystemHealth` function with this (hits /api/health instead of the two backends directly, avoiding CORS):

```javascript
async function checkSystemHealth() {
  try {
    var r = await fetch('/api/health', {signal: AbortSignal.timeout(8000)});
    var d = await r.json();
    if (d.rag && !d.rag.error) {
      document.getElementById('healthRag').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--green)">●</span> RAG: <strong>' + d.rag.known_docs + ' docs</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-dim)">(' + d.rag.documents_table_rows + ' rows)</span>';
    } else {
      document.getElementById('healthRag').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--red)">●</span> RAG: <strong>offline</strong>';
    }
    if (d.llm && !d.llm.error) {
      var memPct = d.llm.memory && d.llm.memory.usage_percent ? d.llm.memory.usage_percent.toFixed(0) + '%' : '?';
      var n = d.llm.models_loaded !== undefined ? d.llm.models_loaded : '?';
      document.getElementById('healthLlm').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--green)">●</span> LLM: <strong>' + n + ' models</strong> <span style="color:var(--text-dim)">(' + memPct + ' RAM)</span>';
    } else {
      document.getElementById('healthLlm').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--red)">●</span> LLM: <strong>offline</strong>';
    }
    if (d.last_ingest) {
      document.getElementById('healthIngest').innerHTML = '🕐 Ingest: ' + d.last_ingest;
    } else {
      document.getElementById('healthIngest').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--text-dim)">🕐 Ingest: unknown</span>';
    }
  } catch (e) {
    document.getElementById('healthRag').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--red)">●</span> RAG: <strong>unreachable</strong>';
    document.getElementById('healthLlm').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--red)">●</span> LLM: <strong>unreachable</strong>';
    document.getElementById('healthIngest').innerHTML = '<span style="color:var(--text-dim)">🕐 Ingest: unknown</span>';
  }
}
```

=== RESTART THE DASHBOARD SERVER ===

The uvicorn process (PID ~12178) runs as a bare nohup, not via the systemd unit (which is dead). Restart with:

```bash
pkill -f 'uvicorn app:app.*8080'
sleep 1
cd ~/agent-activity && nohup /usr/bin/python3 -m uvicorn app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080 > /tmp/dashboard.log 2>&1 &
disown
sleep 2
curl -s http://localhost:8080/api/health | head -10
```

=== SANITY CHECKS BEFORE YOU CALL IT DONE ===

1. `curl -s http://localhost:8080/api/health` returns a JSON body with rag.known_docs as a number AND llm.models_loaded as a number AND last_ingest as an ISO timestamp from today.
2. Open http://192.168.0.195:8080/dashboard.html in a mental model: search box is visible, status/target/project dropdowns are visible, task count badge shows "(N of M)".
3. No JavaScript errors in the browser console (you can tail /tmp/dashboard.log for uvicorn errors, but browser errors are invisible to you — trust the static spec review).

